The article is a statement by the President of the United States, Barack Obama, congratulating David Cameron on becoming the new British Prime Minister. Obama expressed his commitment to the special relationship between the United States and the United Kingdom, stating that there is no closer friend and ally than the UK. He also mentioned his plans to meet with Cameron at the G8/G20 meetings in June and invited him to visit Washington. Obama thanked Gordon Brown for his service as Prime Minister and expressed confidence that the ties between the two countries will continue to thrive in the future.